# ESRD CY21.2 System Architecture

This document contains the System Architecture documentation, reverse engineered from the legacy COBOL ESRD Pricer.

## 1. High-Level Component Diagram
This diagram illustrates the macro-level structure of the ESRD Pricer. [ESDRV212](file:///Users/rohitkelapure/Downloads/ESRDCY212MainframePricerReleaseFiles/ESDRV212) acts as the primary orchestrator, interfacing with various shared datasets (Copybooks) and dispatching to year-specific calculation modules.

```mermaid
graph TD
    classDef main fill:#f9f,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px;
    classDef db fill:#bbf,stroke:#333,stroke-width:1px;
    classDef calc fill:#bfb,stroke:#333,stroke-width:1px;
    
    Ext[External FISS System] -->|Passes BILLCPY & RTCCPY Data| Driver(ESDRV212 Driver)
    class Driver main
    
    subgraph Data Copylibs
        WAGE[WAGECPY]
        RTC[RTCCPY]
        BILL[BILLCPY]
        BILL --> WAGE
    end
    class WAGE,RTC,BILL db
    
    subgraph Reference Tables
        ESCHI[ESCHI151 - Childrens Hosp]
        ESWRT[ESWRT151 - MSA Wage]
        ESCOM[ESCOM151 - Composite CBSA]
        ESBUN[ESBUN210 - Bundled CBSA]
    end
    class ESCHI,ESWRT,ESCOM,ESBUN db
    
    Driver -->|Loads| ESCHI
    Driver -->|Loads| ESWRT
    Driver -->|Loads| ESCOM
    Driver -->|Loads| ESBUN
    
    subgraph Calculation Engines
        C15[ESCAL151]
        C16[ESCAL160]
        C17[ESCAL170/171]
        C18[ESCAL180]
        C19[ESCAL191]
        C20[ESCAL200/202]
        C21[ESCAL212...]
    end
    class C15,C16,C17,C18,C19,C20,C21 calc
    
    Driver -->|Dispatches based on B-THRU-DATE| C21
    
    C21 -->|Returns PPS-DATA-ALL & RTC| Driver
    Driver -->|Returns Final Calculation| Ext
```

## 2. Sequence Diagram: Primary Execution Flow
This sequence diagram details the runtime execution path for a standard 2021 claim entering the [ESDRV212](file:///Users/rohitkelapure/Downloads/ESRDCY212MainframePricerReleaseFiles/ESDRV212) driver.

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant FISS as FISS (Calling System)
    participant DRV as ESDRV212 (Driver)
    participant CALC as ESCAL212 (CY2021 Calculator)
    
    FISS->>DRV: Invoke with BILL-NEW-DATA & PPS-DATA-ALL
    activate DRV
    Note over DRV: 0100-ENTER-DRIVER
    DRV->>DRV: Initialize Variables (Clear PPS-DATA-ALL)
    DRV->>DRV: Check Initial Validations (DRV-001, DRV-002)
    
    alt Pre-2011 Blended Override (DRV-003)
        DRV->>FISS: Return Early with Payment Exception (RTC 01)
    else 2011-2013 Pacific Island Override (DRV-004)
        DRV->>FISS: Return Early with Payment Exception (RTC 01)
    else Standard Execution Route
        note over DRV: 0800-FIND-BUNDLED-CBSA-WI
        DRV->>DRV: Search ESBUN210 Table for Wage Index
        note over DRV: Dispatch Logic (DRV-005)
        
        alt B-THRU-DATE in 2021
            DRV->>CALC: CALL ESCAL212 USING BILL-NEW-DATA, PPS-DATA-ALL, WAGE-REC
            activate CALC
            CALC->>CALC: Execute Pricing Calculation Logic
            CALC-->>DRV: Return updated PPS-DATA-ALL & Return Code (RTC)
            deactivate CALC
            
            DRV-->>FISS: Return Final Payment / Reject Code
        end
    end
    deactivate DRV
```

## 3. Sequence Diagram: Internal Calculation Engine Flow (ESCAL212)
This sequence diagram details the V2 internal calculation methodology after [ESDRV212](file:///Users/rohitkelapure/Downloads/ESRDCY212MainframePricerReleaseFiles/ESDRV212) routes the claim to the [ESCAL212](file:///Users/rohitkelapure/Downloads/ESRDCY212MainframePricerReleaseFiles/ESCAL212) module.

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant DRV as ESDRV212 (Driver)
    participant VAL as Validation (1000-)
    participant INIT as Initialization (1200-)
    participant CALC as Computation (2000-)
    
    DRV->>VAL: Invoke ESCAL212 Component
    activate VAL
    VAL->>VAL: Validate Claim Elements (CAL-001)
    
    alt Validation Failure (e.g. Invalid DOB/Height/Weight)
        VAL-->>DRV: Return early with specific error code
    else Validation Success
        VAL->>INIT: Pass control
        activate INIT
        INIT->>INIT: Clear Working Storage Hold Variables
        INIT->>INIT: Base Wage Initiation (CAL-002)
        INIT->>CALC: Dispatch to Bundled Factors (2000-)
        deactivate INIT
        activate CALC
        CALC->>CALC: Apply Age Multiplier (CAL-003)
        CALC->>CALC: Apply BSA Math & Factor (CAL-004)
        CALC->>CALC: Apply Low BMI Check & Factor (CAL-005)
        CALC->>CALC: Apply Onset Time Adjustments
        CALC->>CALC: Calculate Comorbid Multipliers
        CALC->>CALC: Aggregate Adjusted Base Rate
        CALC-->>DRV: Return Fully Priced Payload
        deactivate CALC
    end
    deactivate VAL
```
